# .cursorrules - ABR Real Estate Management System

## Project Context
This is the ABR Society & Real Estate Management System.
- Frontend: Angular 17+ with standalone components, Angular Material, Reactive Forms
- Backend: ASP.NET Core 8 Web API, Entity Framework Core 8, PostgreSQL 15
- Architecture: Clean Architecture (Controller -> Service -> Repository -> EF Core)
- Auth: JWT Bearer tokens, BCrypt password hashing, hardware fingerprint security
- Deployment: Portable USB pendrive - offline only, no internet required

## Coding Standards
- Angular: use standalone components, inject() function (not constructor injection)
- Angular: use Signals for reactive state where possible
- C#: follow Clean Architecture - no business logic in controllers
- C#: all repository methods must be async/await
- Database: all tables use UUID primary keys (gen_random_uuid())
- All amounts stored as DECIMAL(15,2) - never float or double
- Soft deletes: use is_deleted + deleted_at columns - never hard delete
- All API responses use standardized ApiResponse<T> wrapper
- Error handling: global exception middleware in ASP.NET Core
- Validation: FluentValidation for all DTOs

## Naming Conventions
- Angular components: kebab-case files, PascalCase class
- Angular services: feature.service.ts
- C# classes: PascalCase, interfaces prefix I
- Database tables: snake_case (e.g., daily_entries)
- API endpoints: /api/{resource} (plural, lowercase)

## Do Not
- Never use localStorage - use in-memory services only
- Never expose connection strings in frontend code
- Never return passwords or password hashes in API responses
- Never use float/double for money - always decimal
